
The quick way:
  
  python setup.py build
  sudo python setup.py install
  python setup.py docs #<- optional
  cd examples/basic
  lighttpd -Df lighttpd.conf


Building and installing:

  Run setup.py with the build command:
    $ python setup.py build
  
  Then install the fcgi.so library:
    $ sudo python setup.py install
  

Generating documentation:

  ...simply by running:
    $ python setup.py docs
  This command will generate API documentation
  in HTML format and put it in doc/api/.
  
  You need to install the extension before generating
  documentation.


